## Lists are Mutable

Lists are **changed in place**!




:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="50%"}

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.python .cell-code}
lst[1]
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
'math'
```
:::

```{.python .cell-code}
lst[1] = "stats"
lst
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
['data', 'stats', 34, True]
```
:::
:::

:::


::: {.column width="50%"}

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.python .cell-code}
lst[2:] = [False, 77]
lst
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
['data', 'stats', False, 77]
```
:::
:::

:::
::::


::: notes
If we change any element value in a list, the list itself will be changed as well.
